---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  description="Privacy policy for SeniorPath."
  title="Privacy Policy"
>
  <section class="section">
    <article class="article-shell">
      <header class="article-header">
        <p class="article-kicker">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="article-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="article-excerpt">
          This page explains what data SeniorPath may store locally and how site-level interactions are handled.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="article-prose">
        <h2>Local storage</h2>
        <p>
          SeniorPath stores small pieces of information in your browser to preserve theme preference and guide completion
          state. This helps keep the experience consistent between visits on the same device.
        </p>

        <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
        <p>
          If analytics or external services are introduced later, this policy should be updated to describe what is
          collected, why it is collected, and how it is retained.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          Links to the practice app or other external tools may be governed by separate privacy terms and policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Updates</h2>
        <p>
          This policy may be revised as the product changes. Material updates should be reflected on this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
